<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99038282355952></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99038282355952><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99038282355952>well, sorry, here's 1-10</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=99038282355952#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=2424><span id= >Zemplokazo</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>11 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 20th 2:20 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay, by request I'll give some more input into these levels.&nbsp;&nbsp;The early stages of your character are important, but primarily there are probably dozens of ways to do these levels per starting town and it's usually pretty basic.  Until after 10, almost any class can be soloing, mages soloing to 10 is a walk in the park.  But it is boring.  Anyway, okay, here's what I've got to say about 1-10...<br><br>1-3: Welcome to your newbie garden- When you start out after you do the guild note stuff, (I'd recomend putting some points into your first melee skill so that you can hit better, but it's not REALLY needed) and go out of your city and get to know your newbie zone.  Some of the easiest to navigate and kill in are Freeport (west and east) and Greater Faydark.  Some tougher zones to navigate and operate in are Oggok, Grobb, Halas, Cablis.  Neriak can be tough to get around in but Nektulos forest is good.  When you get outside, /con the first critter you find.  If it's red or yellow then stay away, it will kill you more likely then not.  If it's an even fight, attack and hopefully kill it.  Alrighty, only 9 more even kills to go until you level (A little more if you're a Barbarian, iksar, ogre, troll or iksar, and a little less if you're playing a halfling.)  Kill the even stuff until you're lvl 2, then move onto killing even and blue monsters.  Some kinds of mobs might group up on you, trial and error will show you this.  You might die, you might not, it's no big deal if you do.  Get to level 3 killing mainly lv 1 and 2 critters, lv 3 mobs are usually hard to find.<br><br>4-8:  Okay, you're starting to get a little farther in life, but you still need to get your corpse really fast if you die, cause it wont stay long at all until lv 6.  If you're around Greater Fay, you can start fighting at Orc Hill.  The orcs here may con too high for you, look for anything even or under if you're a melee type, anything yellow or under if you're a pet class.  Another place to try is Lesser Fay, there is lots to hunt here around 4th and up.  These early levels are pretty much find something, kill it, sit, get up and do it again.  If you cant find anything to give you good EXP, settle for slow advancment or move to another zone.  Make sure to keep on top of new skills and spells.  Aorund 6th you can hunt in Crushbone (CB) some, keep any CB belts you find, there is a good quest in Kaladim for them.  They can also sell to other players for 1pp each, but they can be very hard to sell at times.  Also keep bonechips you find, whole stacks can sell to players for 2-4pp, or you can do another quest in kaladim for EXP and some minor coin and items.  These levels will not be too fast but they won't be difficult.  Money will probably get tight around 8th level, but spells are fun.<br><br>8-10+:  Around this levels, casters get some fun new spells and new options are opened.  Mages and especially necro's can solo quite well with lvl 8 spells, my necro could solo red Scarabs in north ro at 8th, but it was hard.  For most people, NRO is still a little too high for soloing, but there are some grouping opportunites here.  Dervish camps provide good EXP and money, if you can get into a good group.  Also, at 8th you can go to the Siren Rocks in Ocean of Tears and kill the Aqua goblins until 10th, when most classes can kill the Alluring Sirens, which are good and very very boring EXP.  At 10th you could also try Unrest, there is good EXP to be found there but it can be very dangerous.  Just push through these levels, they fun is yet to come.  <br><br>Good luck with your mage or necro or monk or whatever!  Have fun.<br><br>~Zemplokazo<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
